Package: croquis
Title: Transit Sketch Planning with GTFS
Version: 0.1,0
Authors@R: 
    person("Julian", "Villafuerte Diaz", , "contact@julian.city", role = c("aut", "cre"),
    comment=c(ORCID="0000-0001-6543-7105"))
Description: Tools for rapidly creating detailed and realistic transit networks and schedules in GTFS format, including a front-end Shiny app called Croquis. Introduces the Simplified Speed and Frequency Structure (ssfs), a data structure that simplifies GTFS creation and editing. Includes functions for conversion between SSFS and GTFS formats. Includes a calibration engine which adjusts SSFS speeds based on a reference GTFS. Output GTFS are compatible with travel demand and accessibility analysis tools such as r5r.
License: `use_mit_license()`
